  "prompt": "What is the difference between true love and attachment?",
  "response": "Here are key differences between true love and attachment:\n\nTrue Love:\n1. Unconditional and selfless\n2. Allows personal growth\n3. Supports partner's happiness\n4. Focuses on giving\n5. Respects individual boundaries\n6. Builds mutual trust and understanding\n7. Accepts partner's flaws\n8. Prioritizes partner's well-being\n9. Emotionally mature and balanced\n10. Based on genuine care and compassion\n\nAttachment:\n1. Conditional and possessive\n2. Restricts personal growth\n3. Seeks control and validation\n4. Focuses on receiving\n5. Creates dependency\n6. Driven by fear of loss\n7. Wants to change partner\n8. Prioritizes personal needs\n9. Often emotionally unstable\n10. Based on personal insecurities\n\nTrue love is about supporting and nurturing each other, while attachment is more about meeting personal emotional needs and maintaining control. True love allows freedom and individual identity, whereas attachment tends to be restrictive and clingy.\n\nTrue love comes from a place of emotional health and self-awareness, while attachment often stems from unresolved personal issues and insecurities.",
